  <string id="clan_prus_5.name" text="Barten"/>
  <string id="clan_prus_5.text" text="The Bartians are an Old Prussian tribe settled in the forested hills and river valleys south of Natangia, centered around what is now northern Poland. In the middle of the 13th century, they live under clan-based leadership and uphold traditional pagan practices, while showing increasing interactions with neighboring Polish territories due to geographical proximity. This contact influences aspects of their trade and political affairs, introducing occasional diplomatic ties and cultural exchanges alongside ongoing conflicts. Bartian warriors are known for their skill in forest warfare and defensive tactics, and their society thrives on agriculture, hunting, and maintaining strong local identities despite external pressures from both the Teutonic Order and Polish interests."/>
  <string id="clan_prus_6.name" text="Sambia"/>
  <string id="clan_prus_6.text" text="The Sambians are an Old Prussian tribe residing on the Sambia Peninsula along the southeastern coast of the Baltic Sea, in what is now the Kaliningrad region of Russia. In the middle of the 13th century, they are distinguished by their prominent role in regional trade, benefiting from their strategic coastal position and access to maritime routes. Their society is organized around clan leadership and deeply rooted pagan traditions, while their economy is supported by fishing, agriculture, and commerce with neighboring peoples. Although they maintain capable warriors to defend their territory, the Sambians are noted for their relative openness to foreign merchants and their reputation as skilled negotiators in matters of trade and diplomacy."/>
